Field Detail

FLOW_CANCEL_EVENT

static final String FLOW_CANCEL_EVENT
The event ID that flow context widget can process to cancel the given number of last flows. The event parameter is a positive integer indicating how many steps back the flow should return. If the integer is greater than the number of opened flows, all child flows will be closed, keeping just the flow container (the menu). If the integer is zero or less, no changes will be done.

Since:
2.0
See Also:
Constant Field Values
Method Detail

setAllowFlowCancelEvent

void setAllowFlowCancelEvent(boolean allowFlowCancelEvent)
The setter for controlling whether FLOW_CANCEL_EVENT is allowed to be processed. By default, depending on the implementation, the event should be allowed. This method can be called to turn it off, e.g. for security purposes.

Parameters:
allowFlowCancelEvent - A Boolean indicating whether FLOW_CANCEL_EVENT is allowed.
Since:
2.0
